			<CASNumber>7664-41-7</CASNumber>
			<common:generalComment xml:lang="en">Liquid ammonia is a colorless liquid with a strong pungent odor. Ammonia, as an important chemical raw material, is usually pressurized or cooled to obtain liquid ammonia for convenient transportation and storage. Liquid ammonia is easily soluble in water and forms ammonium ions NH4+and hydroxide ions OH -, resulting in an alkaline solution. Liquid ammonia is mostly stored in pressure resistant steel cylinders or tanks, and cannot coexist with substances such as acetaldehyde, acrolein, boron, etc. Liquid ammonia is widely used in industry, which is corrosive and easily volatile, resulting in a high incidence of chemical accidents.</common:generalComment>
			<common:generalComment xml:lang="zh">液氨是一种无色液体，具有强烈的刺激性气味。氨作为一种重要的化工原料，通常通过加压或冷却来获得液氨，以方便运输和储存。液氨易溶于水，形成铵离子 NH4+ 和氢氧根离子 OH -，形成碱性溶液。液氨多储存在耐压钢瓶或钢罐中，不能与乙醛、丙烯醛、硼等物质共存。液氨在工业中应用广泛，具有腐蚀性，易挥发，导致化学事故高发。</common:generalComment>
